Belkin has launched the first Apple-approved battery pack with a Lightning port input for charging. The 10,000mAh battery pack charges using Appleâ€™s Lightning connector, meaning iPhone users can plug the pack into the same cable they use to charge their phone. Called the BoostCharge Power Bank Lightning 10K, it features two USB Type-A ports as output, with one outputting 2.4A and one 1A. The device costs $59.99. The BoostCharge Power Bank Lightning 10K is currently available for pre-order from the Belkin website.